<li class="ql-align-justify">I have proofread my essay</li>
<li class="ql-align-justify">The verb tense is the same throughout</li>
<li class="ql-align-justify">There are no fragments or run-on sentences</li>
<li class="ql-align-justify">All punctuation is correct</li>
<li class="ql-align-justify">Every word is spelled correctly</li>
<li class="ql-align-justify">I have had at least one other person read my essay for content, style, and grammar</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Resume/CV</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>My contact information includes a phone number and professional email address</li>
<li>My “Education” section includes all relevant information:</li>
<li>School name(s), location, and dates attended</li>
<li>Degree type(s) and area(s) of study</li>
<li>GPA (if higher than 3.0 or equivalent)</li>
<li>Class ranking (if in top 20%)</li>
<li>Awards with dates (if not including a separate “Awards” section)</li>
<li>School activities with roles and dates (if not including a separate “Activities” section)</li>
<li>For graduate applicants:</li>
<li>Thesis titles(s) have been included (if not in separate “Publications” section)</li>
<li>My “Experience” section includes all relevant information:</li>
<li>Position(s), company name(s), and dates employed</li>
<li>I have used position subsections (if promoted or changed positions)</li>
<li>I have included 2+ bullet points per position that highlight my responsibilities and achievements</li>
<li>Each bullet begins with a strong verb</li>
<li>I have included quantitative data whenever possible</li>
<li>My positions have been listed in reverse-chronological order</li>
<li>My “Skills/Achievements/Awards” section includes all relevant information:</li>
<li>I have included all languages, computer, software, and industry-specific skills I possess, including levels of proficiency</li>
<li>I have included all awards with dates, including relevant responsibilities or achievements that led to receiving the award (if not included in “Education” section)</li>
<li>I have included important academic or career achievements I have met, including relevant responsibilities (if not listed in “Experience” section)</li>
<li>I have included an “Interests” section (if space allows)</li>
<li>Any publications I have included follow proper formatting rules, my name has been bolded, and hyperlinks have been added when possible</li>
<li>All of my experiences, achievements, responsibilities, etc. are in the correct verb tense, with present tense only used for those that I’m currently engaged in</li>
<li>My resume/CV fits within the length and page margin limits</li>
<li>I have used appropriate resume/CV formatting, making it easy to skim for information</li>
<li>The formatting I have used is consistent throughout the entire resume/CV </li>
<li>Someone has reviewed my resume/CV for grammatical and formatting errors</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Activities List (for undergraduate applicants)</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>I have included up to 10 activities, including activity type, grade level participation, and length of time</li>
<li>My activity descriptions are as specific as possible and avoid redundancy</li>
<li>My activity descriptions use active verbs and limit the use of adjectives and adverbs</li>
<li>My activity descriptions include quantitative data to support my achievements and responsibilities</li>
<li>My activities are listed in order of importance</li>
</ul>
